==English==
{{wikipedia}}

===Etymology===
From {{etyl|enm|en}}, from {{etyl|ang|en}} {{term|his||his, its|lang=ang}}, from {{etyl|gem-pro|en}} {{term/t|gem-pro|*hes||of this}}, genitive of {{term/t|gem-pro|*hiz||this, this one}}, from {{etyl|ine-pro|en}} {{term/t|ine-pro|*ḱe-}}, {{term/t|ine-pro|*ḱey-||this}}. Cognate with {{etyl|da|-}}, {{etyl|sv|-}}, {{etyl|no|-}}, {{etyl|is|-}} {{term|hans||his|lang=is}}. More at {{l|en|he}}.

===Pronunciation===
* {{IPA|/hɪz/}}, {{X-SAMPA|/hIz/}}
* {{audio|en-us-his.ogg|Audio (US)}}
* {{rhymes|ɪz}}

===Pronoun===
{{en-pron|desc=possessive pronoun}}

# {{context|attributive|lang=en}} Belonging to [[him]].
#* '''1596''', {{w|Edmund Spenser}}, ''{{w|The Faerie Queene}}'', IV.i:
#*: With that he put '''his''' spurres vnto his steed, / With speare in rest, and toward him did fare, / Like shaft out of a bow preuenting speed.
#*{{quote-book|year=1898|author={{w|Winston Churchill (novelist)|Winston Churchill}}
|title={{w|The Celebrity}}|chapter=4
|passage=No matter how early I came down, I would find him on the veranda, smoking cigarettes, or otherwise '''his''' man would be there with a message to say that '''his''' master would shortly join me if I would kindly wait.}}
#* '''2011''', Xan Rice, ''The Guardian'', 8 Apr 2011:
#*: In '''his''' first televised address since the siege in Abidjan began this week, Ouattara said he would focus on returning the country to normal to ease the plight of civilians.
# {{context|obsolete|lang=en}} [[its|Its]]; belonging to it. (Now only when implying personification.) {{defdate|11th-17th c.}}
#* '''1603''', {{w|John Florio}}, translating {{w|Michel de Montaigne}}, ''Essays'', II.2:
#*: My stomacke could not well reach so farre: it is very much troubled to come to an end of that which it takes for '''his''' need.
#* '''1611''', Matthew 5:13, King James Version:
#*: Ye are the salt of the earth: but if the salt have lost '''his''' savour, wherewith shall it be salted?
# {{context|archaic|lang=en}} Used erroneously in place of ''’s'' after a noun, especially a masculine noun ending in {{g|s}}, to express the possessive case.
#: ''Ahab '''his''' mark'' for ''Ahab's mark''.

====Usage notes====
* When followed by a noun, it is sometimes referred to as a ''possessive adjective'', qualifying the following noun. It is, however, the [[possessive case]] of the personal pronoun [[he]].

